1
00:00:00,010 --> 00:00:01,790
Allah, Exalted and Glorious is He, said:

2
00:00:01,790 --> 00:00:10,070
"And they will approach one another, inquiring of each other."

3
00:00:10,070 --> 00:00:11,110
Who are these people?

4
00:00:11,110 --> 00:00:11,830
The people of Paradise.

5
00:00:11,830 --> 00:00:12,910
May Allah make us among them.

6
00:00:12,910 --> 00:00:14,090
O Allah, make us among them.

7
00:00:14,090 --> 00:00:23,370
"And they will approach one another, inquiring of each other."

8
00:00:23,370 --> 00:00:33,190
They will say, "Indeed, we were previously among our people fearful [of displeasing Allah]."

9
00:00:33,190 --> 00:00:46,650
"So Allah conferred favor upon us"

10
00:00:46,650 --> 00:00:52,910
"and protected us from the punishment of the Scorching Fire."

11
00:00:53,650 --> 00:01:00,730
"Indeed, we used to supplicate Him before."

12
00:01:00,730 --> 00:01:07,990
"Indeed, it is He who is the Beneficent, the Merciful."

13
00:01:10,090 --> 00:01:11,880
Allah Almighty says:

14
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:17,440
"Whoever does righteousness - it is for his [own] soul;"

15
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:23,500
"and whoever does evil [does so] against it."

16
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:31,140
"And your Lord is not ever unjust to [His] servants."

17
00:01:31,140 --> 00:01:35,220
Allah Almighty has also repeated this verse in Surah Al-Jathiyah:

18
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:40,340
"Whoever does a good deed - it is for himself;"

19
00:01:40,340 --> 00:01:47,300
"and whoever does evil - it is against the soul."

20
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:59,920
"Then to your Lord you will be returned."

21
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:59,920
The one who did righteous deeds returns to Allah Almighty and enters Paradise.

22
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:05,640
And the one who did evil deeds returns to Allah Almighty and enters the Fire.

23
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:12,260
"Certainly did Allah confer [great] favor upon the believers"

24
00:02:12,260 --> 00:02:18,000
"when He sent among them a Messenger from themselves,"

25
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:21,720
"reciting to them His verses"

26
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:24,080
"and purifying them"

27
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:27,640
"and teaching them the Book and wisdom,"

28
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:34,580
"although they had been before in manifest error."

29
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:41,280
"There has certainly come to you a Messenger from among yourselves."

30
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:45,520
"Grievous to him is what you suffer;"

31
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:50,580
"[he is] concerned over you and to the believers"

32
00:02:50,580 --> 00:02:53,540
"is kind and merciful."

33
00:02:54,580 --> 00:02:58,460
As for the criminal on the Day of Resurrection:

34
00:02:58,460 --> 00:03:01,000
"The Day the Horn will be blown. And We will gather the criminals,"

35
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:05,480
"that Day, blue-eyed."

36
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:07,320
By Allah, I read its interpretation:

37
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:10,400
"Blue-eyed" means their faces will be blackened,

38
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:15,200
and their eyes blue from the intensity of fear and the terrors of the Day of Resurrection.

39
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:18,120
O my brothers, Allah Almighty says:

40
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:21,000
"The criminals will be known by their marks,"

41
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:27,000
"and they will be seized by the forelocks and the feet."

42
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,680
Their faces blackened,

43
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:30,660
their eyes blue,

44
00:03:30,660 --> 00:03:33,560
shackled by their feet,

45
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:34,880
together with their hands.

46
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:36,760
We ask Allah for safety and well-being.

47
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:39,960
For this reason, Allah Almighty tells us:

48
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:45,900
"And fear a Day when no soul will suffice for another soul at all,"

49
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:50,580
"nor will intercession be accepted from it,"

50
00:03:50,580 --> 00:03:54,280
"nor will compensation be taken from it,"

51
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:57,780
By Allah, no ransom will be taken from you, even if it were an earth full [of gold].

52
00:03:57,780 --> 00:04:02,960
By Allah, no ransom will be taken from you, even if it were your father,

53
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,480
or your mother.

54
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:05,960
Allah Almighty says:

55
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:08,140
"They will be shown each other."

56
00:04:08,140 --> 00:04:10,860
"The criminal will wish that he could be ransomed"

57
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:16,120
"from the punishment of that Day by his children,"

58
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,839
"And his wife"

59
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:19,100
Meaning his spouse,

60
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:22,480
"and his brother,"

61
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:26,480
"And his nearest kindred who shelter him,"

62
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:34,740
"And whoever is on earth entirely [so] then it could save him."

63
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:36,920
Because of this, Allah said:

64
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:44,500
"And fear a Day when no soul will suffice for another soul at all,"

65
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:49,700
"nor will intercession be accepted from it,"

66
00:04:50,260 --> 00:05:00,200
"nor will compensation be taken from it, nor will they be aided."

67
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:15,220
"[It will be] on the Day the earth will be replaced by another earth, and the heavens [as well],"

68
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:22,020
"and all creatures will come out before Allah, the One, the Prevailing."

69
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:29,500
"The Day when We will fold the heaven like the folding of a [written] sheet for the records."

70
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:35,460
"As We began the first creation, We will repeat it."

71
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:38,400
"[That is] a promise binding upon Us."

72
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:51,180
"A promise binding upon Us. Indeed, We will do it."

73
00:05:51,180 --> 00:05:57,060
"When the sky breaks apart,"

74
00:05:57,060 --> 00:06:01,860
"And when the stars fall, scattering,"

75
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:04,980
"And when the seas are erupted,"

76
00:06:04,980 --> 00:06:07,960
"And when the [contents of] graves are scattered,"

77
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:12,660
"A soul will [then] know what it has put forth and kept back."

78
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:15,600
"And when Paradise is brought near,"

79
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:18,680
"And when Hellfire is set ablaze,"

80
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:24,360
"A soul will [then] know what it has brought [with it]."

81
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:30,280
A soul will know what it has brought.

82
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:33,580
Therefore, on the Day of Resurrection,

83
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:36,720
Allah Almighty said about that great Day:

84
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:42,400
"No! When the earth has been leveled - pounded and crushed -"

85
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:48,120
"And your Lord has come and the angels, rank upon rank,"

86
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:53,500
"And Hell is brought [near] that Day."

87
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:56,420
It has seventy thousand reins,

88
00:06:56,420 --> 00:07:00,800
and on every rein are seventy thousand angels dragging it,

89
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:04,220
so that it does not erupt upon the people of the gathering.

90
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:06,580
We ask Allah for safety and well-being.

91
00:07:06,580 --> 00:07:10,200
"And Hell is brought [near] that Day."

92
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:18,020
"That Day, man will remember,"

93
00:07:21,540 --> 00:07:24,400
"but how [i.e., what good] to him will be the remembrance?"

94
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:30,600
"He will say, 'Oh, I wish I had sent ahead [some good] for my life.'"

95
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:35,860
Oh, I wish I had prepared for that great Day.

96
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:39,420
So for that reason, we want to prepare ourselves from now.

97
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:42,660
"And Hell is brought [near] that Day."

98
00:07:42,660 --> 00:07:45,020
What is the food of the people of Hell?

99
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:48,120
We ask Allah for safety and well-being.

100
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:53,760
"Indeed, the tree of Zaqqum"

101
00:07:53,760 --> 00:08:00,000
"is food for the sinful."

102
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:05,360
"Like murky oil, it boils within bellies"

103
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:09,660
"like the boiling of scalding water."

104
00:08:09,660 --> 00:08:13,300
"And you will see the people [as if] intoxicated"

105
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:19,600
"while they are not intoxicated; but the punishment of Allah is severe."

106
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:49,480
"Then He causes his death and provides a grave for him."

107
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:55,300
"Then, when He wills, He will resurrect him."

108
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:59,200
Listen to what Allah Almighty said about our creation:

109
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:04,080
"And certainly did We create man from an extract of clay."

110
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,700
This is my story and yours.

111
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:11,520
"Then We placed him as a sperm-drop in a firm lodging."

112
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:17,140
"Then We made the sperm-drop into a clinging clot,"

113
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:20,260
"and We made the clot into a lump [of flesh],"

114
00:09:20,260 --> 00:09:23,580
"and We made [from] the lump, bones,"

115
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:26,660
"and We covered the bones with flesh;"

116
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:32,700
"then We developed him into another creation."

117
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:37,820
"So blessed is Allah, the best of creators."

118
00:09:37,820 --> 00:09:38,960
This is in this world.

119
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:45,440
"Then indeed, after that you are to die."

120
00:09:45,910 --> 00:09:54,800
"Then indeed you, on the Day of Resurrection, will be resurrected."

121
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:57,340
By Allah, my brothers, we will be resurrected.

122
00:09:57,510 --> 00:09:59,300
Allah Almighty says:

123
00:09:59,670 --> 00:10:03,400
"And the Horn will be blown,"

124
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:10,300
"and whoever is in the heavens and whoever is on the earth will fall dead"

125
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:14,500
"except whom Allah wills."

126
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:19,000
"Then it will be blown again,"

127
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:25,180
"and at once they will be standing, looking on."

128
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:27,160
The Horn will be blown,

129
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:31,960
"and suddenly they will be [alert] upon the earth's surface."

130
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:34,700
The Horn will be blown,

131
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:41,560
"and at once they will be standing, looking on."

132
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:43,600
The Horn will be blown,

133
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:51,860
"and suddenly they will be hastening from the graves to their Lord."

134
00:10:51,860 --> 00:10:54,500
"They will say, 'O woe to us!"

135
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:59,340
"Who has raised us up from our sleeping place?'"

136
00:10:59,340 --> 00:11:05,300
"[The reply will be], 'This is what the Most Merciful had promised,"

137
00:11:10,180 --> 00:11:14,340
"and the messengers told the truth.'"

138
00:11:15,140 --> 00:11:26,340
"It will not be but one blast,"

139
00:11:26,340 --> 00:11:35,340
"and at once they are all brought present before Us."

140
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,840
Brought present before Allah.

141
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:43,440
"Their eyes humbled,"

142
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:46,100
"humiliation will cover them."

143
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:56,440
"That is the Day which they had been promised."

144
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:59,080
Allah Almighty says:

145
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:02,140
"And they ask you about the mountains,"

146
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:06,240
"so say, 'My Lord will blow them away with a blast.'"

147
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:10,980
"'And He will leave the earth a level plain;'"

148
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:15,340
"'you will not see therein a depression or an elevation.'"

149
00:12:15,340 --> 00:12:16,480
On the Day of Resurrection,

150
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:21,300
"That Day, they will follow the caller [with] no deviation therefrom,"

151
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:28,060
"and [all] voices will be stilled before the Most Merciful,"

152
00:12:28,060 --> 00:12:31,860
"so you will not hear except a whisper [of footsteps]."

153
00:12:31,860 --> 00:12:36,000
"That Day, no intercession will benefit"

154
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:40,920
"That Day, no intercession will benefit"

155
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:46,200
"except [that of] one to whom the Most Merciful has given permission"

156
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,520
"and has accepted his word."

157
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:54,500
"That Day, no intercession will benefit"

158
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:59,460
"except [that of] one to whom the Most Merciful has given permission"

159
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:02,520
"and has accepted his word."

160
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:08,700
"He knows what is [presently] before them and what will be after them,"

161
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:11,500
By Allah, I read the interpretation earlier:

162
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:14,660
"He knows what is before them"

163
00:13:14,660 --> 00:13:16,440
On the Day of Resurrection,

164
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:18,840
Allah knows your destiny,

165
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,400
whether you are in Paradise.

166
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:23,080
And Allah knows your destiny whether you are in the Fire.

167
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:28,000
"He knows what is before them and what will be after them,"

168
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:32,040
"but they do not encompass it in knowledge."

169
00:13:32,780 --> 00:13:37,480
"And [all] faces will be humbled before the Ever-Living, the Sustainer of existence."

170
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:44,960
"And [all] faces will be humbled before the Ever-Living, the Sustainer of existence."

171
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:51,780
"And he will have failed who carries injustice."

172
00:13:52,110 --> 00:13:57,580
"But he who does of righteous deeds while he is a believer"

173
00:13:58,330 --> 00:14:02,700
"he will neither fear injustice nor deprivation."

174
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:05,220
Allah will not wrong you, by Allah.

175
00:14:05,220 --> 00:14:06,940
He will not decrease [your reward],

176
00:14:06,940 --> 00:14:09,260
Allah Almighty will not wrong you,

177
00:14:09,260 --> 00:14:11,080
nor will He add to your bad deeds,

178
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,780
nor will Allah Almighty deprive you of your right.

179
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:17,100
Rather, He increases your good deeds until you enter Paradise.

180
00:14:18,220 --> 00:14:19,160
So my brothers,

181
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:22,600
The Day of Resurrection, if you knew of its terror,

182
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:27,240
You would flee from your family and homelands.

183
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:32,980
The Day the sky splits apart from its terror,

184
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:37,920
And the hair of the children turns white from it.

185
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:42,280
A frowning, severe Day, its evil

186
00:14:44,540 --> 00:14:52,300
Spreading among creation, of great magnitude.

187
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:57,180
These people on the Day of Gathering will be divided into two groups:

188
00:14:57,180 --> 00:15:05,660
"And the Day the Hour appears - that Day they will become separated."

189
00:15:05,660 --> 00:15:11,200
"And as for those who had believed and done righteous deeds,"

190
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:16,240
"they will be in a garden [of Paradise], delighted."

191
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:23,260
"But as for those who disbelieved and denied Our verses"

192
00:15:23,260 --> 00:15:33,440
"and the meeting of the Hereafter, those will be brought into the punishment."